## 3. ACL strategy per actor

Every encrypted handle must be granted to (a) `address(this)` via `FHE.allowThis(handle)` immediately after assignment, and (b) every actor that will later read it via `FHE.allow(handle, actor)`. Missing grants surface as runtime ACL reverts on the relayer.

| Actor | Reads which slots | Grant pattern |
|-------|-------------------|---------------|
{{ACL_TABLE}}

> **Rule:** the contract itself ALWAYS gets `FHE.allowThis(handle)` after every encrypted write. Forgetting this is the #1 cause of "decryption fails on Sepolia but works locally" bugs. The `/zama-contract` generator injects these automatically — but document the intent here so future humans don't strip them.

